During March and April 1924, the Sydney Mail devoted a number of issues to the visiting Special Service Squadron. Even the advertisers joined the bandwagon! <a href="http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=ecwzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=2712%2C3793932" rel="nofollow">news.google.com/newspapers?id=ecwzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDA...</a> 

The issues of 9 and 16, April covered the Squadron's visit to Sydney 
<a href="http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=ecwzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=6417%2C3629491" rel="nofollow">news.google.com/newspapers?id=ecwzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDA...</a> ; <a href="http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=eswzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=6445%2C3925093" rel="nofollow">news.google.com/newspapers?id=eswzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDA...</a> (this issue also featured the scuttling of HMAS Australia I) ; but the March issues were also full of pics and other items <a href="http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=eMwzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=1390%2C2661541" rel="nofollow">news.google.com/newspapers?id=eMwzAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=IZYDA...</a> ;
